alias.description: Specify an alias for a register or data channel

abs.description: The absolute value of the number

and.description: Logical AND, one if both op2 and op3 are true, zero otherwise

bap.description: Jump to op4 if op1 op2 with precision op3

bapal.description: Jump to op4 if op1 op2 with precision op3, writing the address of the next line to ra

bapz.description: Jump to op3 if op1 0 with precision op2

bapzal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 0 with precision op2, writing the address of the next line to ra

bdns.description: Jump to op2 if op1 channel is not configured

bdnsal.description: Jump to op2 if channel op1 is not configured, writing next line address to ra

bdse.description: Jump to op2 if channel op1 is configured

bdseal.description: Jump to op2 if channel op1 is configured with next line address written to ra

beq.description: Jump to op3 if op1 = op2

beqal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 = op2, writing the address of the next line to ra

beqzal.description: Jump to op2 if op1 = 0, writing the address of the next line to ra

bge.description: Jump to op3 if op1 >= op2

bgeal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 >= op2, writing next line address to ra

bgezal.description: Jump to op2 if op1 >= 0, writing next line address to ra

bgt.description: Jump to op3 if op1 > op2

bgtal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 > op2, writing next line address to ra

bgtzal.description: Jump to op2 if op1 > 0, writing the address of the next line to ra

ble.description: Jump to op3 if op1 <= op2

bleal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 <= op2, writing next line address to ra

blezal.description: Jump to op2 if op1 <= 0, writing the address of the next line to ra

blt.description: Jump to op3 if op1 < op2

bltal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 < op2, writing the address of the next line to ra

bltzal.description: Jump to op2 if op1 < 0, writing the address of the next line to ra

bna.description: Jump to op4 if op1 ~= op2 with precision op3

bnaal.description: Jump to op4 if op1 ~= op2 with precision op3, writing next line address to ra

bnaz.description: Jump to op3 if op1 ~= 0 with precision op2

bnazal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 ~= 0 with precision op2, writing next line address to ra

bne.description: Jump to op3 if op1 != op2

bneal.description: Jump to op3 if op1 != op2, writing next line address to ra

bnezal.description: Jump to op2 if op1 != 0, writing the address of the next line to ra

brap.description: Relative jump to +op4 if op1 op2 with precision op3

brapz.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 0 with precision op2

brdns.description: Relative jump to +op2 if channel op1 is not configured

brdse.description: Relative jump to +op2 if channel op1 is configured

breq.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 = op2

brge.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 >= op2

brgt.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 > op2

brle.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 <= op2

brlt.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 < op2

brna.description: Relative jump to +op4 if op1 op2 with precision op3

brnaz.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 0 with precision op2

brne.description: Relative jump to +op3 if op1 != op2

define.description: Set a name for the constant

hcf.description: Stop work and burn the microprocessor

jal.description: Jump to op1, writing the address of the next line to ra

l.description: Reading the value of parameter op3 from port op2

lr.description: Read reagent value op4 in op3 mode from port op2

ls.description: Read value op4 from slot op3 of port op2

mod.description: Remainder of integer division of op2 by op3 (the result is not equivalent to the % operator, and will be positive for any signs of op2 and op3)

nor.description: Inverse OR, one if both op2 and op3 are false, zero otherwise

or.description: Logical OR, zero if both op2 and op3 are false, one otherwise

peek.description: Push the top value off the stack into op1 without moving the stack

pop.description: Pop a value from the stack and write to op1

s.description: Writing a value to the op2 parameter of port op1

sap.description: If op2 op3 with precision op4, then one, otherwise zero

sapz.description: If op2 0 with precision op3, then one, otherwise zero

sdns.description: If channel op2 is not set to one, otherwise zero

sdse.description: If channel op2 is set to one, otherwise zero

select.description: Ternary select. If op2 is true then op1 := op3, otherwise op1 := op4

seq.description: If op2 = op3, then one, otherwise zero

seqz.description: If op2 = 0, then one, otherwise zero

sge.description: If op2 op3, then one, otherwise zero

sgez.description: If op2 0, then one, otherwise zero

sgt.description: If op2 > op3, then one, otherwise zero

sgtz.description: If op2 > 0, then one, otherwise zero

sle.description: If op2 op3, then one, otherwise zero

sleep.description: Pause the program for op1 seconds

slez.description: If op2 0, then one, otherwise zero

slt.description: If op2 < op3, then one, otherwise zero

sltz.description: If op2 < 0, then one, otherwise zero

sna.description: If op2 op3 with precision op4, then one, otherwise zero

snaz.description: If op2 0 with precision op3, then one, otherwise zero

sne.description: If op2 op3, then one, otherwise zero

snez.description: If op2 0, then one, otherwise zero

xor.description: XOR, one if one and only one of op2 and op3 is true, zero otherwise

yield.description: Pausing the program until the next tick

Charge.description: Battery or accumulator charge, J. Level of electricity generation by a solar panel, W.

Class.description: the class of the object in the slot

Color.description: Color of LED lamp, fixed beacon and LED display

Combustion.description: 1 - ignition detected, 0 - in all other cases

ElevatorLevel.description: For reading - the level at which the elevator cabin is located, or -1 if there is no cabin. On record - sends the elevator to the specified floor.

ElevatorSpeed.description: The speed of the elevator cabin, m / tick. A negative value corresponds to downward movement, 0 to a stationary booth, a positive value to upward movement.

ExportCount.description: counter of objects passed through the export slot

Filtration.description: Switches the filtration of the spent mixture in a durable suit.

ForceWrite.description: Forces the write and multiwrite chips to transfer the current value to the hardware.

Harvest.description: Activates harvesting in an automatic hydroponic station.

Horizontal.description: angle with respect to the Sun in degrees in the horizontal projection of the Sun onto the sensor plane

Idle.description: Loading the arc furnace. 0 - ore is not loaded, 1 - loaded.

ImportCount.description: counter of objects passed through the import slot

Maximum.description: The maximum value of some equipment parameter, such as battery charge or pressure at the inlet to the combustion chamber of a jet engine. Very often present but not used.

MaxQuantity.description: maximum number of items in a slot

Output.description:
For a sorter - r/w , Int - the next output to which the object will be issued.
For a stacker - w, Trigger - unloads the accumulated packing of objects into the export slot.

Plant.description: Starts the process of planting a plant from the import slot in an automatic hydroponic station.

PositionY.description: Y coordinate of the current position

PositionZ.description: Z coordinate of the current position

Power.description: 0 - no power or off, 1 - power on

PowerActual.description: Total electricity consumption by all devices in the network, W.

PowerGeneration.description: Current generation of electricity by the generator, W.

PowerRequired.description: The total electricity demand of all devices in the network, W.

PressureExternal.description: atmospheric pressure in the environment, kPa

PressureInternal.description: The pressure in the pipeline at which the operation of active ventilation stops, kPa. Installed but not used.

Ratio.description:
For batteries - Charge/Maximum ratio.
For other devices - Setting/Maximum ratio.

Reagents.description: total weight of ingredients in grams

RequiredPower.description: The energy required for the operation of the device, W.

Setting.description: The current value of some hardware parameter. The type and possible values ​​depend on the hardware.

SolarAngle.description: angle relative to the sun in degrees

TemperatureExternal.description: temperature of the external atmosphere, K

TemperatureSetting.description: The specified temperature inside the durable suit, K.

TotalMoles.description: The total amount of gas inside the pipeline, mol.

VelocityRelativeX.description: speed of movement along the X coordinate

Vertical.description: angle relative to the sun in degrees

ChargeRatio.description: The battery level in the slot.

Efficiency.description: Plant growth efficiency in an automatic hydroponic station. -1 if there is no plant.

Growth.description: Plant growth stage in automatic hydroponic station. -1 if there is no plant.

Health.description: Plant health in an automatic hydroponic station. 0 - dead plant, 1 - completely healthy, -1 - no plant.

Mature.description: Readiness of the plant in the automatic hydroponic station for harvesting. -1 if there is no plant.

OccupantHash.description: hash of the object in the slot

PressureAir.description: Pressure in the cylinder with the breathing mixture of the suit installed in the rack, kPa.

PressureWaste.description: Pressure in the cylinder with the spent mixture of the suit installed in the rack, kPa.

lb.description: Batch read in op1 from all devices with hash op2 of parameter op3 in op4 mode

sb.description: Batch write to all devices with hash op1 to parameter op2 of value op3

stack.description: Populates the stack with argument values

Throttle.description: Sets the throttle of Combustion Centrifuge.

CombustionLimiter.description: Sets the combustion limiter of Combustion Centrifuge.
